    "exptext": "<b>Kali Temple at Dakshineswar — Swami Vivekananda founded Ramakrishna Mission (1897)</b><br><br><b>Ramakrishna Paramahansa</b> lived and worshipped at the <b>Kali temple of Dakshineswar</b>, located on the <b>eastern bank of the Hooghly River</b> near Kolkata. The presiding deity is <b>Bhavatarini</b>, an aspect of Kali.<br><br>He saw in all forms of worship the adoration of one <b>Supreme Being</b> and regarded all religions as <b>different paths leading to the same goal</b>. He drew spiritual inspiration from the <b>Vedanta and the Upanishads</b>. He himself founded the <b>Ramakrishna Math</b> with his monastic disciples.<br><br><b>Swami Vivekananda (1863–1902)</b> formed the <b>Ramakrishna Mission in 1897</b>, after the death of Ramakrishna, to carry out <b>philanthropic and charitable works</b>. Its headquarters is at <b>Belur, near Kolkata</b>.<br><br>The Mission:<br>• Stands for <b>religious and social reforms</b><br>• Is based on <b>Vedantic doctrines</b><br>• Runs many <b>schools and hospitals</b> and helps society during natural calamities",
