    "quesimage": "",
    "exptext": "<b>E.V. Ramaswamy Naicker (Periyar) — to awaken non-Brahmins and expose Brahmin tyranny (1925)</b><br><br>The anti-Brahmin crusade got further impetus when <b>E.V. Ramaswamy Naicker</b>, popularly known as <b>Periyar</b>, joined the anti-Brahmin movement. He had actively participated in the <b>Non-Cooperation movement</b> and even served as <b>President of the Tamil Nadu Congress</b> before quitting the party in <b>1924</b> over differences on social justice and representation of non-Brahmins.<br><br>After leaving the Congress, Periyar launched the <b>Self-Respect Movement (1925)</b> aimed at:<br>• Awakening <b>non-Brahmins</b><br>• Improving the <b>living conditions of the Dravidian people</b><br>• Exposing <b>Brahmin tyranny</b> and the deceptive methods by which Brahmins controlled all spheres of Hindu life<br><br>He tried to provide an umbrella movement to all non-Brahmins of South India, particularly <b>Tamil Nadu</b>.",
