    "quesimage": "",
    "exptext": "<b>Separate electorates for untouchables (depressed classes)</b><br><br>During the <b>second half of 1932</b>, <b>Ramsay MacDonald's Communal Award</b> created <b>separate electorates for untouchables</b>. <b>Gandhiji</b> began a <b>fast unto death on 20th September 1932</b> opposing this provision and was able to secure an agreement through the <b>Poona Pact signed on 24th September 1932</b>.<br><br>The pact retained the <b>Hindu joint electorate</b> with <b>reserved seats for untouchables</b>, who were given <b>greater representation</b> than awarded by MacDonald.<br><br>Gandhiji started the <b>All-India Anti-Untouchability League / Harijan Sevak Sangh in September 1932</b> for medical education and technical facilities for Harijans. In <b>1933</b>, he founded the weekly journal <b>Harijan</b>. He also undertook a <b>12,500 miles Harijan Tour between 1933 and August 1934</b>.<br><br>The Congress passed a key resolution at its <b>Karachi Session of 1931</b> calling for equal access to <b>public employment, roads, wells and schools</b> regardless of caste.",
